ted<br />\nStates. In a Chinese literature review that identified 279 studies including 24,112 patients with DILI, tuberculostatics<br />\ncomplementary and alternative medicines (CAMs) were found to be the most common cause of DILI in China.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nK. Chan,1, H.W. Zhang, Z.X. Lin. <em>Treatments Used in Complementary and<br />\nAlternative Medicine</em><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n篇野其中一個author 仲要係中大中醫學院嘅人 <img src=\"/assets/faces/xm/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"35e8cf4d52b17739b1cbb9013fca9c02c4d71cc3","tid":507125,"uid":47359,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-12-23T03:59:05.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>Liver injury Drug-induced liver injury (DILI) is always a challenging problem to health care professionals worldwide.<br />\nRecent studies have demonstrated that DILI in Asia has etiologies different from those in Europe or United<br />\nStates. In a Chinese literature review that identified 279 studies including 24,112 patients with DILI, tuberculostatics<br />\ncomplementary and alternative medicines (CAMs) were found to be the most common cause of DILI in China.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nK. Chan,1, H.W. Zhang, Z.X. Lin. <em>Treatments Used in Complementary and<br />\nAlternative Medicine</em><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n篇野其中一個author 仲要係中大中醫學院嘅人 <img src=\"/assets/faces/xm/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n更加有說服力"},{"pid":"eeb311e3972a70345d783e5744f7e7a34762a910","tid":507125,"uid":42767,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-12-23T04:00:54.000Z","msg":"link: <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780444634078000484\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FB9780444634078000484&d=%2F%2B5%2Bqc2hEJKMc6pdDVG3IzANphTrK3OAdhrcB0lChBw%3D&h=2eedcc5d\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780444634078000484</a>"},{"pid":"1c88bc4012c